  "methods_notes": "Table 4 reports subgroup-specific comparisons of Fri13 vs. all other Fridays on national daily accident counts, partitioned into 8 subgroups (severity x2, age x4, time-of-day x2). For each subgroup we report the crude rate ratio with Welch two-sample t-test raw p, the Bonferroni-adjusted p (alpha_family=0.050, threshold=0.00625), and a covariate-adjusted NB2 count ratio from a national-level NB2 model with year, month, weekday, and holiday controls; alpha was estimated by MLE. All 8 subgroups use the same national-level NB2 specification for direct comparability. Prefecture-level heterogeneity for the overall is_fri13 estimand is reported separately in Figure S3 (Phase 2C-C4)."
